gy\n\nn/a\n\n### Description\n\nIn Carbon's Empty states page, it says \"an empty state for a table would replace the table and the column headers and footer should not be present.\" The reason for hiding the column headers is to avoid \"having a screen reader read the entire table before getting to the message that there is no content in the table.\"\r\n<img width=\"922\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40870771/155029822-41dceed1-d6b3-488e-a3e9-94e03554c3ce.png\">\r\nColumn headers are important for sighted users. It shows you what the platform could look like once you‚Äôve input more of your data. [This article](https://userpilot.com/blog/bad-ux-design/) even suggests that empty states should always be replaced with demo content.\r\nWe can hide column headers from a screen reader and display it visually, use the aria-hidden attribute and set it to true.\n\n### WCAG 2.1 Violation\n\n_No response_\n\n### CodeSandbox example\n\nn/a\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nn/a\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/carbon-design-system/carbon/blob/f555616971a03fd454c0f4daea184adf41fff05b/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)\n- [X] I checked the [current issues](https://github.com/carbon-design-system/carbon/issues) for duplicate problems","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/carbon-design-system/carbon/issues/10813/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/carbon-design-system/carbon/issues/10813/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null,"score":1}]}}